<subsection xml:id="C25.S11.SS10">
<title>Further Series Representations</title>          
<para xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="46" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="25.11.35" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S11.E35">\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^{n}}{(n+a)^{s}}=\frac{1}{\Gamma\left(s\right)} \int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{x^{s-1}e^{-ax}}{1+e^{-x}}\mathrm{d}x=2^{-s}\left(\zeta \left(s,\tfrac{1}{2}a\right)-\zeta\left(s,\tfrac{1}{2}(1+a)\right)\right), if \Re a&gt;0, \Re s&gt;0; or \Re a=0, \Im a\neq 0, 0&lt;\Re s&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="47" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2.m1">a=1</Math> , (25.11.35) reduces to (25.2.3).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="48" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="25.11.36" mode="display" xml:id="C25.S11.E36">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{\chi(n)}{n^{s}}=k^{-s}\sum_{r=1}^{k}\chi(r)\zeta\left (s,\frac{r}{k}\right), if \Re s&gt;1,</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2.m2">\chi(n)</Math> is a Dirichlet character <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p2.m3">\pmod{k}</Math> (§27.8).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="49" xml:id="C25.S11.SS10.p3.s1">
See also Srivastava and Choi (2001).
</sentence>

</para>
 
